-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
                Details about what's changed
----------------------------------------------------------------------------

1) VisItDataWriter now can write one layer of ghosts for the data written for
visualization.  The ghost data will not be plotted but can be used by VisIt's
internal calculations for things such as the rendering of surfaces at patch
boundaries.

To enable this, call the new method in VisItWriter "setWriteGhosts" with an
argument of true.  When using this functionality, make sure that ghosts have
been filled before each call to writePlotData(). 



